Ad Text:
Location: Mawson Lakes, SA (preferred) | Other locations considered | Telework available

Own and lead enterprise systems architecture and backend configuration for sustainment applications, with a strong focus on Microsoft Dynamics ERP. This is a hands-on technical leadership role, driving integration, automation and digital transformation across complex environments.

You will remain technically engaged while leading a small specialist team delivering enterprise sustainment systems that meet business and contractual requirements.

 

What You’ll Do

Lead systems architecture for sustainment software and ERP platforms

Own Microsoft Dynamics backend configuration, customisation and integration

Solve complex integration and process issues across enterprise systems

Deliver sustainment applications using Agile and DevSecOps (CI/CD) practices

Execute the Digital Transformation Roadmap for sustainment tools

Integrate ERP systems with Enterprise IT and engineering platforms

Provide technical leadership and mentoring across architecture and DevSecOps

 

About You

You are a senior systems architect or enterprise applications lead with strong experience in ERP systems, Microsoft Dynamics, backend configuration and system integration. You enjoy solving complex technical problems and staying hands-on while leading delivery.

Essential:

Strong experience in systems architecture and enterprise application integration

Hands-on experience configuring Microsoft Dynamics

On-premises installation of Business Central (BC), Customer Engagement (CE), and ERP systems

Development experience and strong understanding of SDLC best practices

Delivery experience using Agile and DevSecOps (CI/CD)

Strong background in software configuration management and application lifecycle management.

Clear, confident communication with technical and business stakeholders

Desirable:

Experience in Moodle and VetTrak

Experience in PsiGen PsiCapture (OCR, Document Automation, Process Automation)

Dashboarding and reporting experience

Jira / Confluence (Atlassian)

AWS or cloud platform experience

 

At Lockheed Martin Australia, we believe that when people are empowered, inspired, and supported, they can achieve extraordinary things. We embrace flexibility, so our people can be their best inside and outside of work. We champion inclusion and continuous learning, ensuring all voices are heard and valued. And we thrive on collaboration, turning challenges into opportunities for growth and innovation.  As a leader in national security, our innovative and diverse programs create a more secure future for Australia across space, air, land, sea, and cyber domains. Every day is a chance to solve the world’s most complex challenges and make a profound impact. Experience it here.




A Veteran-Friendly Workplace

Veterans and transitioning service members are encouraged to apply. Lockheed Martin Australia is recognised as a Veteran Friendly Employer.

 

How we reward and support you

When you join Lockheed Martin, you work on projects you won’t experience anywhere else. We offer a range of benefits to suit all life stages:

Flexible & hybrid work options

Online discounts program offering immediate savings or cashback

Leave options including Purchase Leave

Additional benefits such as Novated Leasing and Fitness Programs

Learning & Development platforms for ongoing self-development

Special Requirements

Applicants must be eligible to obtain and maintain an Australian Defence Security Clearance and employment may be contingent on the provision of further personal information including citizenship to ensure compliance with international export control legislation and regulations.

 Equal Opportunity Statement

Lockheed Martin Australia supports Equal Employment Opportunity and values diversity in the workplace by creating a place of employment that is, free of unlawful discrimination and is harassment free, fair, ethical, inclusive, and values the contribution of all its employees. By leveraging our employees’ unique talents and experiences, we will deliver innovative, affordable solutions and unparalleled customer value.

As part of our endeavours to increase participation of Indigenous Australians, we welcome applications from all people, including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people.

We are committed to creating a workplace where everyone can thrive. If you are selected for this role, we would be happy to discuss any accommodations that will help you to be successful.

Job Title: Data Engineering Specialist (Melbourne or Hobart location)
Ad Text:
About us

At CareSuper, we believe we’re Super Together. As a profit-to-member super fund with over 550,000 members and $63 billion in assets, we’re passionate about helping our members retire with confidence. We’re growing fast and looking for our next superhero to join us on this exciting journey.

About the role

As our new Data Engineering Specialist, you’ll be part of our Technology Delivery team. Reporting to the Manager - Enterprise Systems, you will be responsible for the ongoing development of our data warehouse. You will provide direction and support for data engineering solutions and processes, in accordance with our Data strategy and roadmap.

A day in the life may look like;

Providing technical and strategic advice to senior management, staff and other stakeholders relating to all aspects of Care Super’s data warehouse
Troubleshooting BI and data engineering tools, systems, and software and performance-tune these applications, as necessary.
Producing and reviewing technical documentation and business requirements and analyse business data sources.
Providing support and guidance in the use and development of a variety of BI and data engineering tools.
Completing escalated level 3 requests and providing support to the Insights and Analytics team to resolve data queries.
What we’re looking for

Our ideal candidate will bring extensive experience in database design and integration experience with SQL Server databases. You’ll also bring the below skills;

Relational Database and SQL Language
Extraction, Transformation and Loading (ETL) (Microsoft SSIS)
Data Warehouse / Solution Design
Exposure to Analytics / OLAP Cube Development (Microsoft SSAS Tabular, PowerBI and MDX)
Knowledge of Agile development methodologies and best practices
Report Development (Microsoft SSRS)/BI Dashboards/KPIs
CI/CD processes
C# and nUnit
Why CareSuper?

We’re not just another super fund. We’re a values-driven organisation that puts people first—our members and our team. Here’s what you can look forward to:

Hybrid and flexible work environment
3% Superannuation Guarantee (SG) above industry minimum
Matching an additional superannuation salary sacrifice of up to 2%
5 weeks of annual leave
17 weeks of parental leave for all eligible employees
Holistic health and wellbeing support - free annual flu shots, skin checks, Employee Assistance Program
External Employee Coaching Program and Professional Development
Rewards and Recognition Program, as well as employee discounts and cashback offers on a broad range of products and services
Ready to apply?

We’d love to hear from you! Just send through your resume and a cover letter. Be quick—we may close applications early if we find the right person.

What happens next?

Need support during the application or interview process? We’re here to help. Just reach out to your talent partner and let us know how we can make the process work for you.

We’re committed to protecting your privacy—your personal information will be handled with care and in line with our Privacy Policy.

At CareSuper, we know that diverse perspectives make us stronger. We’re proud to foster an inclusive environment where everyone feels welcome, respected, and valued—no matter your background or identity.

The Role:

Can work remotely but must be based and living in Australia

This Senior Axiom Engineer will be responsible for the development and maintenance of regulatory reporting systems, working closely with the Technical Delivery Lead to ensure all deliverables meet architectural, technical, security, and data access standards.

The role is also accountable for conducting unit testing to achieve quality metrics and for proactively identifying and managing data risks while ensuring they are clearly communicated to all relevant parties.

Additionally, this position will oversee the full development life cycle, from initial build through to deployment into Production environments.

What We're Looking For:

Advanced development experience and SME using AxiomSL. 

We are keen to learn about your strong Axiom Developer SME and work with regulatory reporting and risk projects.

V10 and Taxonomy experience is ideal; APRA taxonomy experience is a plus.

Good knowledge of individual Axiom objects (Aggregation, Data Models, Portfolios, Stream and Instance Keys, etc.), including their configurations and settings.

Design and development ability based on business requirements gathering and continuous improvement. 

Manage vendor CV patches and taxonomy upgrades, environment setup, development, and testing tasks through to completion.

Define clear success criteria with a focus on customer service and stakeholder engagement.

Previous experience in Banking or Financial Services organisations is an advantage.

This is a rare and secure job opportunity to join one of Australia's leading banks where you can work autonomously and fully remote from anywhere in Australia.

Senior Azure Integration Developer – Contract

We’re working with a major healthcare transformation program undergoing a large-scale separation. This is a critical integration role supporting the build-out of a new, independent digital environment.

You’ll sit at the centre of a complex integration landscape, designing and building Azure-based integrations while also providing technical oversight and assurance across vendor-delivered solutions.

What you’ll be doing

Designing and building integrations using Azure Integration Services
Developing and governing APIs using C# / .NET
Reviewing and assuring vendor-built integrations against agreed patterns and standards
Producing and maintaining interface specifications and integration documentation
Working closely with architecture, security, and delivery teams
What we’re looking for

Strong hands-on experience with Azure Integration Services (APIM, Logic Apps, Service Bus, Functions, Event Grid, ADF)
Solid C# / .NET API development background
Experience working across complex, enterprise integration environments
Comfortable balancing hands-on delivery with design review and technical assurance
Experience in government, healthcare, or highly regulated environments is advantageous
The details

Contract role aligned to program lifecycle
Hybrid working (Melbourne-based, approx. 3 days onsite)
High-impact, long-term transformation program
If you’re an integration specialist who enjoys building things properly and improving integration quality across large programs, we’d love to hear from you.

Data Engineer ( BigQuery / SQL / Airflow)
Initial 6 month contract (scope to extend / convert)
$700-820 a day including super DOE
Sydney / Hybrid
  
Talent Insights is looking for a mid-level Data Engineer to join a growing Tech company as part of a broader platform and architecture uplift. This is a newly created role, adding capacity to an existing DE function during a period of modernization.
You’ll be working in a hybrid cloud environment, where core systems sit in Azure whilst data platforms and analytics artefacts are built in Google Cloud.
The focus is on strengthening data foundations, modernising pipelines and settling the platform up for future advanced analytics and AI use cases
  
What you’ll be doing

Building and maintaining data pipelines in GCP
Working with bigQuery and Airflow / Cloud Composer
Consuming data from Azure-based systems into GCP
Supporting modern data warehousing and analytics use cases
Contributing to the uplift of legacy eCommerce data foundations
Collaborating closely with engineers, product and technology stakeholders
  
What we’re looking for

Strong hands-on GCP Data Engineering experience
Airflow / Cloud Composer
Python
Solid understanding of data warehousing concepts
Nice to have

Streaming migrations (Kinesis → Pub/Sub)
Azure Data Factory experience
  
This is a complex, fast environment with multiple stakeholders and evolving priorities. Success in this role will come from being delivery focused, adaptable and comfortable navigating ambiguity. Strong communication skills are just as important as technical capability.
Please note that you must have full work rights to be considered for this role.

Apply now using the above link or send your resume to Olivia@talentinsights.com.au

Keywords: Bigquery / ETL / Data Engineering / PubSub / ML / AI / Airflow / dbt / streaming / real-time / Terraform / Kinesis / Azure Data Factory

What's the role?

As the Customer Data and AI Architect, you will play a pivotal senior role in shaping enterprise-wide Customer Data, Analytics and AI capabilities. Reporting to the Head of Domain Architecture – Data, Integration & AI, this role provides technical leadership and strategic direction across customer identity, customer data platforms, analytics and AI/ML.

You will partner closely with senior stakeholders to translate growth, retention and compliance objectives into scalable, privacy-led data solutions. Leading end-to-end architecture and design, you will define future-state customer data and AI architectures, guide transformational programs, and act as the design authority for customer data technologies across the enterprise.

Responsibilities

Lead customer domain strategic transformation programs for data architecture and delivery.

Design and deliver end-to-end customer data solutions across MarTech, AdTech and enterprise data platforms.

Define future-state and transition-state customer data, analytics and AI/ML architectures aligned to the domain roadmap.

Establish architecture patterns for customer identity, profiles, event streaming, decisioning and real-time activation.

Define customer AI strategy and reference architectures, including predictive models, decisioning and responsible AI guardrails.

Provide architecture governance and day-to-day technical leadership across architects, engineers and vendor partners.

Who are you?

An experienced Lead Data Architect with 10+ years in data solution architecture and 5+ years leading enterprise-scale transformations.

Deeply skilled in customer data architecture, modelling and Customer 360 patterns, including identity resolution and ID stitching.

Hands-on with Customer Data Platforms and activation ecosystems (e.g. Adobe Experience Platform, Salesforce Data Cloud, Segment).

Experienced in cloud-based data platforms, streaming and event-driven architectures, and modern data engineering practices.

Knowledgeable in data science, machine learning and AI for customer use cases, with exposure to MLOps and emerging LLM patterns.

A strong communicator and collaborator, comfortable engaging senior stakeholders, leading teams, and clearly articulating complex architecture decisions.

News Benefits

News Benefits is our way of saying thank you to our people for their valued contribution to News, our audiences, clients and communities. Thanking them for the great things they do daily, for the greater good of Australia. Our benefits include:

Exclusively ours - Access to publications and products from across the News Corp family

Health & wellbeing - Advice, support and facilities for healthy minds and bodies (including an onsite gym at our Adelaide, Brisbane & Sydney offices) 

Time off - News offers a range of leave options to support your personal needs and moments that matter in life: Parental leave, Birthday leave, Volunteer leave, Career break and Compassionate leave.

Helping you grow - Development opportunities (including diversity and inclusion - focused education series) and recognition

Financial wellbeing - Support on making the most of your money

Perks & discounts - Exclusive offers across a range of products and services

Giving back - Make a difference to our communities.

Workplace Inclusion and facilities – Engage with your passions through various employee-resource groups and accessibility to multi-faith quiet rooms & parents’ rooms

Who are we?

News Corp Australia is the nation’s most influential media organisation, operating more than 150 household-name brands across print, digital and multimedia. We lead the way in travel, fashion, food, health, homes and lifestyle, and are the largest publisher across print and digital, reaching more than 16 million Australians each month.

What’s next?

Apply now or for more information on careers at News Corp Australia visit www.newscorpaustralia.com/careers

Our Commitment to Diversity, Equity and Inclusion We know that diversity strengthens our teams and newsrooms as we seek to tell stories that represent the diverse communities of Australia that we serve. Our people make us unique and we all have a story. We encourage people of all ages, backgrounds, races, cultures, religions, sexual orientations, abilities and gender identities to apply. Inclusion is important to us and we want everyone at News to bring their whole-selves to work. If you require any accommodations or adjustments throughout the recruitment process, or would like to outline which pronouns you prefer, please feel free to let us know.

If you require any accommodations or adjustments throughout the recruitment process, please feel free to let us know. For more information regarding Diversity, Equity and Inclusion at NewsCorp Australia please visit www.newscorpaustralia.com/careers under the DEI section.

Highlights

Work directly with General Manager driving AI strategy across divisions
Hands-on role building cutting-edge AI solutions, not just coding
Become the go-to AI expert in a forward-thinking finance company

Position summary



Join our dynamic team as an AI Implementation Specialist (Junior) and become the technical engine driving intelligent automation across a leading finance company. In this hands-on role, you'll bridge the gap between business challenges and cutting-edge AI solutions, working directly with the General Manager to deploy Generative AI and automation tools across Sales, Advisory, Marketing, and Analytics divisions. You'll leverage your expertise in LLM APIs such as OpenAI and Anthropic, combined with Python programming and automation platforms like Zapier and Make, to build workflow solutions that enhance efficiency and profitability. Collaborating with our Head Programmer, you'll integrate AI capabilities into our bespoke CRM system, transforming it into an intelligent assistant while applying Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) techniques to enrich data-driven insights. Your strong technical communication skills will be essential as you educate staff on AI adoption, translate complex concepts for non-technical stakeholders, and ensure compliance with Australian financial services data privacy standards. This role demands problem-solving agility, cross-functional collaboration, and a tinkerer's mindset to stay ahead of emerging AI models and technologies. You'll be the subject matter expert on Generative AI, driving innovation and delivering tangible business impact across every division.


About the company



Our goal at Australian Stock Report is to keep you updated about the best market opportunities and to guide you on when and how to capitalise on these opportunities by using our reports. This includes Australian shares price movement and fluctuations along with our expert analysis of the companies we are considering.

We also understand that educating our clients about financial markets may improve their ability to trade regardless of trend and volatility.

With new articles and insights each day, plus a variety of interactive webinars and Q & A sessions you can participate in, the Australian Stock Report really is the number one destination for daily Australian stock market news and consistent share updates.


About the role

Translate business challenges from Analysts and Sales teams into practical AI-driven solutions.
Collaborate with the Head Programmer to integrate AI capabilities into the company's bespoke CRM system.
Design and implement workflow automation using Python and platforms like Zapier or Make.
Develop and deploy Generative AI solutions across Sales, Advisory, Marketing and Analytics divisions.
Serve as the subject matter expert on LLM APIs, RAG implementations and AI automation tools.
Deliver training sessions to staff on AI tool usage, ensuring safe and effective adoption.
Stay current with emerging AI models and technologies to identify new opportunities for business improvement.
Maintain high standards of data privacy and security in line with Australian financial services regulations.
About the candidate

Demonstrated experience working with Large Language Model APIs, particularly OpenAI or Anthropic platforms.
Proficiency in Python programming with a focus on automation and workflow optimisation.
Hands-on experience with automation tools such as Zapier or Make for business process integration.
Knowledge of Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) systems and their practical applications.
Background in traditional coding practices to complement AI implementation work.
Experience integrating AI solutions into CRM systems or similar business platforms.
Strong understanding of data privacy and security requirements within Australian financial services.
Exceptional ability to translate technical AI concepts into clear, jargon-free language for non-technical stakeholders.
Self-directed learner who actively stays current with emerging AI models and technologies.
Proven problem-solving skills with the ability to identify business pain points and design technical solutions.
Experience training or educating staff on new technology tools and systems.
Collaborative mindset with the ability to work effectively across multiple business divisions.
Proactive and entrepreneurial approach to identifying AI opportunities within business operations.
Strong attention to detail and commitment to delivering secure, compliant AI implementations.
Adaptable communicator who can engage effectively with both technical and business-focused team members.

At Intelligen, we’re building something different. Over the past three years, we’ve evolved from a bold startup to a trusted partner for some of Australia’s most complex data transformations. We’ve helped organisations move from legacy to modern platforms, embedded governance into decision-making, and brought AI into the hands of the business - responsibly and at speed.

But we’re just getting started. As we move into our next phase of growth, we’re looking for consultants who don’t just want to deliver great solutions - but help shape the future of data and AI capability across Australia.

Responsibilities

We’re looking for a GCP Data Engineer, based in Sydney, who can design and deliver modern, scalable data solutions on Google Cloud Platform and across multi-cloud environments (GCP, AWS, Azure). This role has a strong focus on GCP-native data services, while remaining flexible across modern data stacks as required by our clients.

You’ll work directly with clients to understand their data challenges, architect and build high-quality pipelines, and support analytics, governance, and AI enablement initiatives. This role blends hands-on engineering with consulting – helping clients realise value at pace while contributing to Intelligen’s growing cloud data engineering capability.

This role is ideal for someone who loves solving complex engineering problems, thrives in cloud-native ecosystems, and wants to work in a high-performing team doing meaningful, future-shaping work.

What You’ll Do
Design, build, and optimise scalable data platforms and pipelines on Google Cloud Platform
Develop robust ingestion, transformation, and orchestration pipelines using BigQuery, Cloud Storage, Dataflow, Dataproc, Composer, and related GCP services
Build high-quality data models to support analytics, reporting, and AI/ML use cases
Implement modern data architecture patterns, including lakehouse and ELT/ETL approaches
Collaborate closely with clients to translate business requirements into well-architected, actionable data solutions
Support or implement dbt, CI/CD pipelines, Git-based workflows, and data engineering best practices
Ensure strong data quality, governance, lineage, security, and performance optimisation within GCP environments
Work alongside analytics, governance, and AI consultants to deliver cohesive, end-to-end solutions
Contribute to reusable assets, accelerators, and internal frameworks that strengthen Intelligen’s GCP capability


Requirements


4–6+ years’ experience in data engineering
Strong hands-on experience with Google Cloud Platform, particularly BigQuery and cloud-native data services
Experience designing and building production-grade data pipelines on GCP
Strong SQL skills and experience building complex data transformations
Familiarity with modern data stacks e.g. Composer, BigQuery, Databricks, Snowflake, dbt
Experience working across the full data lifecycle: ingestion, transformation, modelling & consumption
Knowledge of DevOps concepts, version control, and CI/CD in data environments
Excellent communication, problem-solving, and collaboration skills


Benefits



We’re not just delivering AI and data projects.. we’re humanising them. That means we care deeply about the how, not just the what. We value curiosity, creativity, and a willingness to challenge the status quo. We look for people who are driven to build a business, get curious, and offer opinions and ideas.

You’ll join a team that’s smart, kind, and ambitious. You’ll have real influence - in your projects, your practice, and the broader business. And as we grow, so will you.

Here’s what that looks like:

Grow With Purpose

Structured development pathways so you always know what you’re working toward.
Paid certifications across all major cloud and data technologies — because mastery matters

Ad Text:
Employment Type: full time continuing role
Integration Engineer within our AI and Innovation directorate
Starting Salary $127351-143489 plus generous superannuation and leave loading
Location: Kensington campus in NSW (Hybrid Flexible Working) 2-3 days in the office
 
About UNSW:
 
UNSW isn’t like other places you’ve worked. We’re a large organisation with a diverse and talented community; a community doing extraordinary things. Together, we are driven to be thoughtful, practical, and purposeful in all we do. Taking this combined approach is what makes our work matter. It’s the reason we’re one of the top 50 universities in the world and a member of Australia’s prestigious Group of Eight. If you want a career where you can thrive, be challenged and do meaningful work, you’re in the right place.
 
The Integration Engineer (AI) designs, builds and operates secure, scalable and cost-efficient integrations and AI-aware data flows across UNSW information systems. The role extends existing middleware and iPaaS capabilities to support retrieval-augmented generation (RAG), vector databases, AI gateways, and content-safety controls, enabling responsible use of AI across enterprise applications. Working within the Innovation and Enablement team, the position ensures integrations and AI components are developed and operated in accordance with UNSW IT standards, the UNSW AI Services & Governance Framework, and Australia’s AI Ethics Principles. This position reports to the Technology Manager (AI) within the Innovation and Enablement team and has no direct reports. 
 
Specific accountabilities for this role include:
• Design, implement and operate integrations and AI service interfaces (LLM providers, AI gateways, vector databases, embedding services) within UNSW platforms. 
• Develop RAG ingestion pipelines – data chunking, metadata enrichment, PII minimisation – to ensure quality, privacy and provenance of data used by AI systems. 
• Apply modern CI/CD and GenAIOps/LLMOps practices for integration components and AI artefacts (prompts, connectors, guardrail policies), including automated evaluation and rollback. 
• Identify opportunities where AI-based automations and intelligent routing can improve business processes; propose architectures and guardrails to realise these opportunities. 
• Plan for AI workload capacity and manage cost through monitoring, optimisation and FinOps reporting. 
• Collaborate with solution architects, data engineers and security teams to design and test AI data flows, using quantitative evaluation metrics (accuracy, groundedness, latency, toxicity). 
• Ensure all integrations and AI solutions comply with functional, security and Responsible-AI requirements, including privacy-by-design and human-in-the-loop controls. 
• Provide application and integration support, including incident response for AI-specific failure modes (prompt injection, model drift, bias anomalies). 
• Operate monitoring dashboards and alerts for AI gateways and vector stores; conduct root-cause analysis and coordinate vendor resolution. 
• Track and report AI quality and safety signals (evaluation scores, content flags) and drive remediation or retraining activities. 
• Maintain RAG data freshness and ensure reconciliation of source-of-truth vs retrieval indexes; implement scheduled backfills and PII purges. 
• Extend testing regimes to include prompt and response evaluations, adversarial tests and reproducibility checks; publish release notes with model/prompt versions. 
• Maintain an AI integration catalogue capturing connectors, models, prompts, indexes, guardrail policies and audit metadata. 
• Instrument and report AI performance (latency, cost, accuracy) and recommend tuning to optimise quality and value. 
• Identify and manage AI-related risks (bias, copyright, safety) and work with the AI Governance Lead to apply mitigations. 
• Translate business needs into AI-aware technical requirements, including evaluation KPIs and data readiness criteria. 
• Provide Level 2 and 3 support for integrations, AI connectors and model usage policies. 
• Contribute to the Integration & AI Engineering Playbook, establishing secure coding, prompt pattern and evaluation standards. 
• Engage with key stakeholders to explain AI behaviours, limitations and responsible use expectations; deliver awareness sessions where required. 
• Collaborate with developers to design and deliver RAG or agent-based features and associated safety test plans. 
• Author operational runbooks and end-user guides, including safe and ethical use instructions for AI-enabled integrations. 
 
Who you are:
Relevant tertiary qualification in Information Technology or equivalent experience in application integration and AI-enabled solutions.
Demonstrated experience with middleware/iPaaS platforms (e.g. Azure Integration Services, MuleSoft, Boomi) and APIs.
Experience with building in Power Platform applications like Copilot Studio, Power Apps and Power platform will be pivotal to the role
Understanding of Azure or AWS AI ecosystem, Infrastructure as a Code and building with Agentic AI tools.
Hands-on experience building or supporting AI integration components such as vector databases (Azure AI Search, pgvector, OpenSearch), embedding pipelines and AI gateways.
Proficiency in Python or TypeScript for data transformation, API development and prompt automation.
Familiarity with GenAIOps/LLMOps practices, evaluation metrics, and prompt/version control.
Knowledge of privacy and security requirements under Australian Privacy Principles and UNSW Cyber standards, including PII redaction and data minimisation.
Understanding of event-driven integration patterns (e.g. Kafka, Pub/Sub) for real-time context updates.
Experience with cloud platforms (Azure, AWS, GCP) and AI service APIs.
Excellent analytical and problem-solving skills, strong communication skills, and ability to engage stakeholders effectively.
Demonstrated ability to work collaboratively within an agile team and adapt to changing priorities.
An understanding of and commitment to UNSW’s aims, objectives and values in action, together with relevant policies and guidelines.
Knowledge of health & safety (psychosocial and physical) responsibilities and commitment to attending relevant health and safety training. 
Benefits and Culture:
• Flexible Working Options (work from home, flexible hours etc) 
• Career development opportunities
• 17% Superannuation contributions and additional leave loading payments 
• Additional 3 days of leave over Christmas period
• Discounts and entitlements (retail, education, fitness)
 
For further details on the benefits, please visit https://www.jobs.unsw.edu.au/lifestyle-benefits
 
How to Apply: please apply through the portal, we would like you to submit a full application including resume and addressing the who you are section.
 
Applications close:  Monday 23rd of Feb at 11.30pm

· Employment history and reference checks

· Medical Checks and Assessments
 
Compliance with the necessary combination of these checks is a condition of employment at UNSW.

Job Description

Ad Text:
We are unique

Join an organisation that values your voice, empowers your autonomy, recognises the strength in diversity, and prioritises your well-being while offering attractive remuneration and benefits. Take pride in having a meaningful impact on regional, rural and remote communities while being a pivotal player in the energy industry's future.

About the role

In this role, you'll be responsible for the development, maintenance and ongoing improvement of electric network models, ensuring they remain accurate and fit for purpose. You'll manage a single source of truth for network models and contribute to technical studies and innovative solutions that support evolving network and customer needs. This role has a strong emphasis on data analytics and automation and require proficiency in Python scripting, SQL, and data management fundamentals at a level comparable to a Databricks Data Analyst. The engineer will leverage these skills within Databricks to improve data quality and deliver insights, while continuing to ensure a single source of truth for network model data.

You'll work closely with internal stakeholders, engineers and external partners to deliver modelling services, support planning decisions, and improve network performance across high, medium and low voltage networks.

This is a temporary role for 12 months can be based anywhere within Essential Energy's operational footprint.

You will be responsible for:


Develop, curate, and enhance electric network models using advanced data techniques.
Automate data extraction and transformation processes using Python and SQL to ensure models are built on clean, accurate data.
Utilize Databricks notebooks and workflows to process large datasets and perform analyses. Write efficient Python scripts and SQL queries in the Databricks environment to support network modelling tasks (e.g. load flow analysis, fault level studies) with improved scalability and speed.
Provide modelling and technical analysis to support planning, operational and project requirements.
Improve network model data related to load flows and short circuit studies.
Collate and analyse network and historical data to prepare technical models, case studies and recommendations.
Support load flow and short circuit modelling across distribution and sub-transmission networks.
Implement rigorous data quality checks and validation steps. Ensure that network model datasets meet required standards and are aligned with industry formats (for example, CIM or RAWX) for consistency and interoperability.
Work closely with network planning engineers and data teams to integrate new data sources and analytics methods.
Contribute to innovative solutions that improve how network modelling data is managed, analysed, and utilized across the business, always focusing on data-driven decision-making.
Build and maintain strong relationships with internal teams, stakeholders, regulators and customers.
Actively promote behaviours that support safety, integrity, inclusion and high ethical standards.

About You

You're an electrical engineer with a strong background in power system modelling and analysis, as well as strong python programming and SQL skills. Background in power systems or network modelling (e.g. load flow, protection, or energy network analysis) is expected. Ability to blend domain expertise with programming skills to solve electrical network modelling problems efficiently. Hands-on experience with data analysis or engineering in a Databricks (or similar big-data) environment is desirable, demonstrating ability to manipulate large datasets and implement analytics workflows. You enjoy solving complex technical problems, working collaboratively, and contributing to meaningful outcomes that benefit regional communities.

You will bring:

Experience using power system modelling tools for technical studies (such as load flow, short‑circuit analysis and dynamic simulations).
Knowledge of network design standards, regulatory requirements and industry guidelines.
Experience developing and managing models using industry‑recognised modelling software.
Strong python programming and SQL skills.
Strong analytical, problem‑solving and report‑writing skills.
Well‑developed communication skills and the ability to work effectively with a range of stakeholders.
Strong organisational skills, attention to detail and the ability to manage competing priorities.

Qualifications required

A Bachelor of Engineering (Electrical) or equivalent, meeting the requirements for Professional Engineer membership with Engineers Australia.

Desirable (Preferred Qualifications):

Databricks Certification: Possession of a Databricks Certified Data Analyst (or Data Engineer) certification is highly desirable as a validation of the candidate's expertise. This certification is preferred but not required.
Analytical Toolsets: Familiarity with power system simulation tools (such as PSS®E, SINCAL, PSCAD) is beneficial, but candidates should be especially adept at integrating such tools with data platforms (e.g. using Python APIs or data exports for analysis in Databricks).

Why Essential Energy

Essential Energy provides employees with a broad range of employee benefits through our corporate partnerships with organisations such as Qantas, Optus, NIB and Mildura Health Fund. You will also gain access to our Health and Wellbeing programs including fitness passport. Visit our employee benefits page for more information.

We are proud to be recognised as a WORK180 Endorsed Employer for All Women.

An energy network doesn't just keep the lights on - it's a living system that must adapt to new and emerging technologies while continuing to meet customer needs. At Essential Energy, your expertise will help shape a safer, more resilient network for communities across our footprint.

For further information please contact Mike Firth - Senior Technology Project Manager on 0412 908 346.



Applications close on Sunday 22 February at midnight.

Building a better energy future.

ABOUT THE ROLE:

This is a hands on, high impact role for someone who can architect production grade AI systems, ship read agentic solutions and uplift an existing engineering team to be AI fluent. You will work closely with Product, Engineering and senior stakeholders to define and deliver AI initiatives that are secure, scalable, compliant and commercially viable, not demos or experiments.

RESPONSIBILITIES:

Define patterns for LLM usage, orchestration, evaluation, observability, and security
Establish standards for agentic workflows, RAG, and model integration
Ensure systems are scalable, resilient, and suitable for multi-tenant, regulated environments
Design and deploy agentic AI solutions that automate complex workflows and decision-making
Build intelligent agents that collaborate with existing workflow engines and APIs, rules, and human-in-the-loop systems
Own the full lifecycle: ideation, prototyping, production, monitoring, iteration
Ensure AI outputs are reliable, explainable, and auditable where required
Partner closely with Product, Design, and Leadership to identify high-impact AI opportunities
Translate business problems into practical AI solutions
Collaborate with the Head of Engineering on the AI roadmap, technical strategy, and delivery sequencing
Embed responsible AI practices: privacy, safety, fairness, and compliance
Ensure sensitive customer and identity data is handled securely across AI workflows
Design AI systems with cost efficiency and predictability in mind
Monitor and optimise LLM usage, token consumption, latency, and infrastructure costs
Mentor and upskill the existing engineering team in AI concepts and best practices
  ABOUT YOU:

7+ years in software engineering, including hands-on AI work in production systems
Solid experience with Python and TypeScript
Proven experience deploying at least one production generative AI application
Deep hands-on experience with Large Language Models (OpenAI, Anthropic, AWS Bedrock)
Experience with agentic AI frameworks and orchestration patterns
Comfortable working across backend systems, APIs, and infrastructure
Strong knowledge of RAG architectures, vector databases, embedding models and evals
Prior experience mentoring engineers or leading technical initiatives
  
WHAT'S IN IT FOR YOU?
This business offers hybrid working with plenty of flexibility, career growth opportunities, and a competitive salary with equity options.
  
WHAT'S NEXT?
